HEADWORD: Chrysochlore
<hw>Chrys"o*chlore</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>chryso`s</grk> gold + <grk>chlwro`s</grk> light green: cf. F.
<ets>chrysochlore</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A South African
mole of the genus <gen>Chrysochloris</gen>; the golden mole, the fur of
which reflects brilliant metallic hues of green and gold.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

